# Writing Topic Hub Skills

Skills are organized by category: `skills/topics/`, `skills/platforms/`, `skills/adapters/`.
Each skill lives in `skills/{category}/<skill-name>/` and is a self-contained package
that plugs into the Topic Hub dispatch loop via one of three category interfaces.

## Skill Categories

| Category   | `topichub.category` | Identifying key        | Purpose |
|------------|---------------------|------------------------|---------|
| **type**   | `type`              | `topicType`            | Defines a topic type with lifecycle hooks, field schema, status transitions, and card rendering |
| **platform** | `platform`        | `platform`             | IM platform integration — webhook handling, slash-command parsing, card posting, group management |
| **adapter** | `adapter`          | `sourceSystem`         | External system connector — transforms inbound webhooks into topic events (GitHub, Jira, PagerDuty, …) |

## Skill Manifest (`package.json`)

The manifest is declared in the skill's `package.json` under the `topichub` key.

### Type skill

```json
{
  "name": "my-bug-tracker",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "main": "src/index.ts",
  "topichub": {
    "category": "type",
    "topicType": "bug",
    "hooks": ["onTopicCreated", "onTopicUpdated", "onTopicStatusChanged"],
    "schema": {
      "severity": "string",
      "stepsToReproduce": "string"
    }
  }
}
```

### Platform skill

```json
{
  "name": "lark-platform",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "main": "src/index.ts",
  "topichub": {
    "category": "platform",
    "platform": "lark",
    "capabilities": ["group_management", "push", "commands"],
    "webhookPath": "/webhooks/lark",
    "auth": { "type": "oauth2", "scopes": ["im:message", "im:chat"] }
  }
}
```

### Adapter skill

```json
{
  "name": "github-adapter",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "main": "src/index.ts",
  "topichub": {
    "category": "adapter",
    "sourceSystem": "github",
    "webhookPath": "/webhooks/github",
    "supportedEvents": ["issues.opened", "issues.closed", "pull_request.merged"]
  }
}
```

## SKILL.md Frontmatter

Every skill **should** have a `SKILL.md` file. The YAML frontmatter controls how
the AI agent executor processes dispatches for this skill.

```yaml
---
name: my-bug-tracker
description: Triages incoming bug reports and assigns severity
executor: claude          # claude | cursor | codex | none
maxTurns: 5               # max agent loop iterations
allowedTools:             # MCP tools the agent may call
  - topichub_update_topic
  - topichub_add_timeline
  - topichub_transition_status
---

# System prompt content below the frontmatter

You are a bug-triage agent. When a new bug topic is created, analyse the
description and metadata, then:
1. Set severity to P0–P3.
2. Assign to the on-call engineer if P0/P1.
3. Post a triage summary to the timeline.
```

The Markdown body (everything below the frontmatter) becomes the **system prompt**
passed to the agent executor.

### Event-specific prompts

Add headings of the form `## on<EventName>` to provide per-event instructions:

```markdown
## onTopicCreated
Perform initial triage…

## onTopicStatusChanged
Validate the status transition…
```

## Interface Contracts

### TypeSkill

```typescript
interface TypeSkill {
  manifest: TypeSkillManifest;
  init?(ctx: SkillContext): void;
  onTopicCreated?(ctx: TopicContext): Promise<void> | void;
  onTopicUpdated?(ctx: TopicContext): Promise<void> | void;
  onTopicStatusChanged?(ctx: TopicContext & { from: string; to: string }): Promise<void> | void;
  onTopicAssigned?(ctx: TopicContext & { userId: string }): Promise<void> | void;
  onTopicClosed?(ctx: TopicContext): Promise<void> | void;
  onTopicReopened?(ctx: TopicContext): Promise<void> | void;
  onSignalAttached?(ctx: TopicContext & { signal: any }): Promise<void> | void;
  onTagChanged?(ctx: TopicContext & { added?: string[]; removed?: string[] }): Promise<void> | void;
  renderCard(topic: any): CardData;
  validateMetadata(metadata: unknown): ValidationResult;
}
```

Required exports: `manifest`, `renderCard`, `validateMetadata`.
Lifecycle hooks are optional — only implement the events your skill cares about.

### PlatformSkill

```typescript
interface PlatformSkill {
  manifest: PlatformSkillManifest;
  init?(ctx: SkillContext): void;
  createGroup?(params: CreateGroupParams): Promise<GroupResult>;
  inviteToGroup?(params: { tenantId: string; groupId: string; userIds: string[] }): Promise<void>;
  postCard?(params: PostCardParams): Promise<void>;
  updateCard?(params: PostCardParams): Promise<void>;
  handleWebhook?(payload: unknown, headers: Record<string, string>): Promise<CommandResult | null>;
  sendMessage?(params: { tenantId: string; groupId: string; message: string }): Promise<void>;
  resolveTenantId?(webhookPayload: unknown): Promise<string> | string;
  runSetup?(ctx: SetupContext): Promise<void>;
}
```

The webhook pipeline is: `handleWebhook` → command parsing → routing → response.
`resolveTenantId` must be implemented for multi-tenant webhook dispatch.

### AdapterSkill

```typescript
interface AdapterSkill {
  manifest: AdapterSkillManifest;
  init?(ctx: SkillContext): void;
  transformWebhook(payload: unknown, headers: Record<string, string>): TopicEventPayload | null;
  runSetup?(ctx: SetupContext): Promise<void>;
}
```

`transformWebhook` is **required** — it converts an inbound webhook into a
`TopicEventPayload` (or `null` to ignore the event).

## Publish Workflow

```bash
# Publish all skills in the repo to the server
topichub publish

# What happens:
# 1. CLI scans skills/{topics,platforms,adapters}/<name>/package.json
# 2. Validates manifest against SkillManifestSchema (zod)
# 3. Reads SKILL.md raw content
# 4. Reads entry point source
# 5. POSTs batch to POST /admin/skills/publish
# 6. Server upserts SkillRegistration + enables for tenant
```

Skills are published as a batch per-tenant. The server stores the full
`publishedContent` (manifest, SKILL.md, entry point, supporting files).

## Testing Patterns

### Unit test a type skill

```typescript
import { myBugTracker } from './index';

test('renderCard includes severity badge', () => {
  const card = myBugTracker.renderCard({
    title: 'Login crash',
    status: 'open',
    metadata: { severity: 'P0' },
  });
  expect(card.fields).toContainEqual(
    expect.objectContaining({ label: 'Severity', value: 'P0' }),
  );
});

test('validateMetadata rejects missing severity', () => {
  const result = myBugTracker.validateMetadata({ stepsToReproduce: '…' });
  expect(result.valid).toBe(false);
});
```

### Unit test an adapter skill

```typescript
import { githubAdapter } from './index';

test('transforms issues.opened webhook', () => {
  const payload = githubAdapter.transformWebhook(
    { action: 'opened', issue: { title: 'Bug', html_url: '…' } },
    { 'x-github-event': 'issues' },
  );
  expect(payload).toMatchObject({ type: 'bug', title: 'Bug' });
});

test('ignores unsupported events', () => {
  const payload = githubAdapter.transformWebhook(
    { action: 'labeled' },
    { 'x-github-event': 'issues' },
  );
  expect(payload).toBeNull();
});
```

### Integration test with `topichub serve`

```bash
# Start serve in dev mode (reads skills from disk, hot-reloads SKILL.md)
topichub serve --executor none

# Trigger a dispatch via the server API, then check logs for
# [DISPATCH], [CLAIM], [AGENT], [RESULT] prefixes
```

## File Layout Reference

```
skills/
  topics/
    my-bug-tracker/
      package.json        # manifest with topichub.category = "type"
      SKILL.md            # agent instructions (frontmatter + system prompt)
      src/
        index.ts          # exports: manifest, renderCard, validateMetadata, lifecycle hooks
      tests/
        index.test.ts
  platforms/
    lark-platform/
      ...
  adapters/
    github-adapter/
      ...
```
